{"title":"Welcome to The Curious Piper","markdown":{"yaml":{"draft":true,"title":"Welcome to The Curious Piper","date":"2026-01-02","description":"What this blog is about, and what you can expect next.","categories":["welcome"]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\nWelcome to The Curious Piper. This blog and my YouTube channel are where I share my passion for pipe smoking and document what I learn along the way. Think of it as a friendly workshop and reading nook rolled into one, a place to explore the craft with curiosity, care, and a bit of ritual.\n\nYou can expect posts and videos that dig into the hobby’s rich tapestry, from pipe shapes and materials to the wide world of tobacco varieties and classic blends. I’ll also cover practical topics like packing, lighting, cadence, and simple techniques that help you get the best flavour and comfort from a bowl, especially if you’re just getting started.\n\nAlongside the “how,” I want to explore the “why,” the traditions, culture, and history that make pipe smoking feel timeless. My aim is to create engaging, high-quality content that educates and inspires, whether you’re a beginner, a seasoned enthusiast, or simply curious about what makes this craft so enduring.\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\nWelcome to The Curious Piper. This blog and my YouTube channel are where I share my passion for pipe smoking and document what I learn along the way. Think of it as a friendly workshop and reading nook rolled into one, a place to explore the craft with curiosity, care, and a bit of ritual.\n\nYou can expect posts and videos that dig into the hobby’s rich tapestry, from pipe shapes and materials to the wide world of tobacco varieties and classic blends. I’ll also cover practical topics like packing, lighting, cadence, and simple techniques that help you get the best flavour and comfort from a bowl, especially if you’re just getting started.\n\nAlongside the “how,” I want to explore the “why,” the traditions, culture, and history that